        "content": "<p>After a recent conversation here about functorial definition of schemes, I've got interested in <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/small+presheaf\">small presheaves</a>. It turns out it is a non-trivial question whether a category of small presheaves has some nice categorical properties. For example, Rosick√Ω in <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022404998001467\">this paper</a> gives a criterion for this category to be Cartesian closed.</p>\n<p>Now, I wonder whether the category of small presheaves on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{CRing}^\\mathrm{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9432em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\" style=\"margin-right:0.01597em;\">CRing</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7487em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1473em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">op</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> has some nice categorical properties. Is it Cartesian closed? Is it a pretopos? There is a related <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/questions/201504/when-is-the-category-of-small-presheaves-an-elementary-topos\">Mathoverflow question</a>, but it mainly discusses when the category of small presheaves is a topos.</p>",
